title: For Sale:  Geissele Automatics 2 Stage Trigger (G2S) 4.5lbs 5.56/.308 Rifle Trigger – NEW
postcontent:
$159 shipped

G2S is made with the same tool steel as the SSA and the sears are also wired.  The main differences with the SSA are a different way of holding the hammer pin, different pins, no laser markings and only spot MP check.  Visually, from the outside of the gun there is no difference from the SSA and the feel and reliability is the same. 


1. Performance Advantages for the Shooter
The Geissele G2S has a pull weight of about 4.5lb. 2.5 lbs on the first stage and 2lb on the second stage. The pull weights and sear engagement are non adjustable.
Trigger and hammer are made from quality tool steel
Sear surfaces are cut by a wire edm machine. Sears cut this way are very accurate and the non-directional surface finish of the wire edm gives a smooth trigger pull without the associated grittiness of directional machining marks left by a milling cutter.
The initial force needed to start the disengagement of the sear surfaces is low and the force linearly increases at a low rate. This helps the shot to fall at the initial point of aim and aids in building shooter confidence in his weapons ability to put the rounds where his sight is pointing.
The Geissele G2S trigger allows the shooter to slap through the trigger pull on close in shots but also set up a long range shot with a crisp trigger break.
A full force hammer spring is used for quick locktime and positive ignition of all types of ammo. No lightened hammer spring is used.
The hammer is lighter than a standard hammer. The lightened hammer favorably decreases locktime and increases accuracy of the weapon, especially for snap shots.

2. Advantages for the Armorer
The Geissele G2S is a simple design that is very similar to the original trigger. The number of parts is identical.
There are no adjustment screws to come loose.
All springs are captive; they will not get lost during disassembly in the field
The entire trigger can be dissembled for cleaning (no rivets or staked parts)
The trigger can be installed without removing the safety
Sear engagement is pre-set from the factory.
Hammer and trigger pins are a close slip fit into nominal receiver holes so the trigger can be installed and removed with rudimentary tools.
Triggers come with a slave pin for the trigger/disconnector assembly for easy installation.

3. Safety Advantages
The Geissele G2S is a 2 stage trigger where there is generous overlap of the sear surfaces which contributes to safety and a low tendency of any inadvertent movement of the trigger to discharge the weapon.
The Geissele G2S has a patented pseudo sear that is almost identical to the standard single stage sear. However, this secondary sear has surfaces that never touch during normal operation. This sear prevents the hammer from falling unless the trigger is pulled.
The secondary safety sear contributes to shooter confidence in dynamic/vehicle situations where a fellow shooter’s muzzle may cover him. There is firm knowledge that even with the safety in the fire position the weapon can never discharge unless the trigger is pulled.
Trigger timing is robust and parts have been sized to operate with a certain amount of wear to the working surfaces. The trigger is designed to operate in dusty, abrasive environments that cause wear.

postcontent:
INVENTORY #: G-I-1715

New in box, in new condition. Revolver .357 caliber. Barrel is on the bottom of the gun instead of the top, this causes improved accuracy. 

Defense revolver, offers great concealability thanks to a very unusual profile. The flat cylinder grants maximum comfort. The new Chiappa Rhino barrel is aligned with the bottom most chamber which is the key component to Rhino's tame characteristics. The position of the barrel lowers the center of gravity and yields a centerline of the bore more in line with the shooter's arm allowing for the most natural "point ability" while engaging a target. This characteristic also drastically reduces both recoil and muzzle flip which insures subsequent shots to be on target faster than ever before. The reduction of the recoil allows for the use of ultra light alloys to be used in the construction of the Rhino minimizing any adverse effect. The flat sided cylinder design of the Rhino reduces the typical revolver profile allowing greater concealment. Featuring both double and single action characteristics, the single action is actuated by a hammer cocking device that engages the unexposed hammer to prepare to fire. The versions of 2" Rhino with Double Action only (item codes ending with "D" instead of "DS") do not have an external hammer. All 2" barrel Rhino revolvers are supplied with a beautiful leather holster included.

RHINO revolvers are supplied with the following outfit:

postcontent:
I've been on a mission to find the best 22lr suppressor host.  This was my favorite, until recently.  You can't go wrong with a Ruger MKIII (or MKII).  They are as reliable as anything you'll ever shoot, and they will eat ANY kind of ammo.  This one has had the trigger smoothed out a little, and I've installed a special bushing to disable the really annoying magazine disconnect they "upgraded" this version with. This makes stripping and assembling the weapon much much easier, and also makes the mags drop free instead of having to pull them out.  I left the loaded chamber indicator alone, but you can do away with that as well.  It is a GREAT pistol, but I've decided I favor one that is a little lighter and more compact.  As much as I'd like to, I can't keep them all.  This was a special limited Talo edition.  It has hogue grips, but they have the ruger logo.  It is finished in a very cool matte black.  It came with a mean looking (but completely unnecessary) flash suppressor on it.  Take that off and install your suppressor, and grin every time you shoot it, because it's funny when you mainly just hear the impact of the projectile.  I'm sure it could end up being somewhat collectible, but it is also reliable and accurate...a great shooter.
